article.description: — Trey Jemison tallied 14 points and 13 rebounds to carry UAB to a 63-51 win over UTEP on Friday night.
article.headline: Jemison carries UAB past UTEP 63-51
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Trey Jemison tallied 14 points and 13 rebounds to carry UAB to a 63-51 win over UTEP on Friday night. Quan Jackson had 18 points and six rebounds for UAB (15-2, 8-1 Conference USA), which earned its fifth consecutive win. Michael Ertel added 14 points. Kassim Nicholson had eight rebounds. Souley Boum had 22 points for the Miners (8-9, 4-7). He also had seven turnovers but only three assists. Bryson Williams added 19 points and eight rebounds. Jamal Bieniemy had six rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
